snippet.textDisplay:
Watching Link have his hand so far back on the knife really stresses me out... HOLD CLOSER TO THE BLADE. IT GIVES YOU CONTROL. Don't fear the blade!

Also if you're going to use the knife to slide it in to a pan, use the spine of the blade. If you're using the sharp end you basically just dull your knife.
